<li id="cite_note-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.meforum.org/article/357">What Does Jihad Mean?</a> "For example, <a href="/wiki/Yasir_Arafat" title="Yasir Arafat" class="mw-redirect">Yasir Arafat</a>'s May 1994 call in <a href="/wiki/Johannesburg" title="Johannesburg">Johannesburg</a> for a "jihad to liberate <a href="/wiki/Jerusalem" title="Jerusalem">Jerusalem</a>" was a turning point in the peace process; <a href="/wiki/Israel" title="Israel">Israelis</a> heard him speak about using violence to gain political ends and questioned his peaceable intentions. Both Arafat himself and his aides then clarified that he was speaking about a "peaceful jihad" for Jerusalem."</span></li>
